Ask HN: Is there a “game”/simulator to reallocate/budget government spending?
text:
I thought it might be interesting to spend a little time fiddling with the amount of money that come in to the government and the money that goes out and reorganise it the way I'd like to, and see how much money there would be available for the things I prioritise.

For example it would be interesting to see what happens if all subsidies to fossil fuel companies are cut to zero, if taxes on corporations increased etc etc.

Sort of like a game but with real figures.

Show HN: Remyx.ai – no code, no data AutoML
text:
demo walkthrough: https://youtu.be/7SMySnRRTew?t=39

Quickly customize a vision model without a dataset to start. Just describe your inputs and a dataset will be generated on the fly, model trained in a few minutes. We’ve started with classifiers but planning to expand to other tasks and APIs to fine-tune on your data.

Thoughts? Wanna chat about it? Book a session: https://calendly.com/terry-remyx/feedback

Ask HN: What type of software development won’t AI replace? Or at least later on
text:
It’s given that app development is going to go first, much of it has already been done away not by Ai but low code frameworks.

I have a feeling fundamental software will take a long time. Browser engines, game engines, compilers, os kernels.
